</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-885FEB18-52AD-4E84-9D0F-118EA52307A2" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Before executing any printhead-calibration make sure the installation procedure has performed correctly.
</p></section><section id="GUID-33F6B1AC-42CE-45DC-AE67-6CBF7BEFF4AE" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">To be able to determine the correct waveforms for controlling the dropletsize a minimum number of nozzles needs to be operational. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In most cases this calibration is executed when a new printhead is placed into the printer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case the filling of this new printhead was unsuccessful air might still be present in the printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The main goal of the mentioned procedure is to get possible air out of the printhead.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-F2864082-F34C-4657-B37E-EA7C5343FE90.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
